{"id": 4128, "title": "Ticket #4128: Perform RPATH tricks on python modules for UW-style compiles", "description": "<blockquote>\nIgor pointed out that, to use the python bindings with a tarball-based install, you need to customize both PYTHONPATH (so python finds the module) and LD_LIBRARY_PATH (so the dynamic loader can load the module).\n\n<p>Using RPATH tricks (similar to what we do with libcondor_utils.so already) we could simplify this setup so LD_LIBRARY_PATH doesn't need to be set.  LD_LIBRARY_PATH is the more annoying of the two because, unlike PYTHONPATH, it can't be manipulated during the python runtime.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2014-Jan-02 08:54:34 by bbockelm:</em> <br/>\n\nThis is now done.  If you are using a tarball-based install, then you only need to set PYTHONPATH and not LD_LIBRARY_PATH.\n\n<p>(FWIW, RPATH was set in these libraries - but it was not adjusted for the fact that they live in a different directory from the rest of the condor libraries.)</p></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Feb-26 16:13</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/d09448c21c14344266c41c1fa56bc31807775cde\">[39490]</a></span>: edit 8.1.4 version history item <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4128\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4128'); return false;\" title=\"Perform RPATH tricks on python modules for UW-style compiles\">#4128</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Feb-26 07:53</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon do